President Biden has announced the nomination of Sarah Bloom Raskin as Vice Chair for Supervision of the Board of Governors of the Federal Reserve System, and the nominations of Lisa Cook and Philip Jefferson to serve on the Board of Governors. The President believes that the Federal Reserve plays a crucial role in achieving maximum sustainable employment and price stability in the economy. The nominations aim to bring a diverse group of individuals with experience, judgment, and talent to lead the Federal Reserve during the current economic recovery. The Senate has already confirmed three of the nominees, and if all five are confirmed, the Board will have a majority of women and increased diversity. President Biden is confident that these nominees, along with Chair Powell and Dr. Brainard, will provide the strong leadership needed to guide the Federal Reserve and help build a better economy for working families. The article provides background information on each of the nominees, highlighting their qualifications and expertise in economics and finance.